2Experience with Computer Telephony Integration (CTI) with CRM application. \u2022Must have experience with Voice Applications integration protocols such as (VXML) and Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR). \u2022Demonstrated ability to create system architecture diagrams and documentation for review by both technical and non-technical audiences. \u2022Experience with the Java/JEE application along with API integrations. \u2022Proactivity communicate application design and architectural with technical teams and vendors. \u2022Demonstrate skills in exercising initiative, good judgment, and making sound technical decisions \u2022Effective verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills to interact with all levels of management. \u2022Ability to break down complex application requirements and propose appropriate architectural solutions. \u2022Mentor, coach and influence architecture and design group discussions. \u2022A minimum of 5-6 yrs. of application architecture experience, along with 10 years of development experience.  Desired : \u2022Advanced degree in a related field. \u2022Knowledge of The Open Group Architecture Framework (TOGAF) v9. \u2022Experience with other cloud architectural to support Cloud environment. Hours : 8:00am - 4:30pm, Monday-Friday Location : 820 Follin Lane, Vienna, VA 22180 Equal Employment Opportunity     Navy Federal values, celebrates, and enacts diversity in the workplace. Navy Federal takes affirmative action to employ and advance in employment qualified individuals with disabilities, disabled veterans, Armed Forces service medal veterans, recently separated veterans, and other protected veterans. EOE/AA/M/F/Veteran/Disability Disclaimer Navy Federal reserves the right to fill this role at a higher/lower grade level based on business need. Bank Secrecy Act Remains cognizant of and adheres to Navy Federal policies and procedures, and regulations pertaining to the Bank Secrecy Act.     Recommended skills  Genesys  Architecture  Int