{"title": "VMware Engineer III", "company": "Navy Federal Credit Union", "description": " YOUR LIFE'S MISSION: POSSIBLE     You have goals, dreams, hobbies and things you\u2019re passionate about. What\u2019s Important to You Is Important to Us We\u2019re looking for people who not only want to do meaningful, challenging work, keep their skills sharp and move ahead, but who also take time for the things that matter to them\u2014friends, family and passions. And we're looking for team members who are passionate about our mission\u2014making a difference in military members' and their families' lives. Together, we can make it happen. Don\u2019t take our word for it.  FORTUNE 100 Best Companies to Work For\u00ae  Computerworld\u00ae Best Places to Work in IT  FORTUNE\u00ae Best Workplaces for Millennials  Forbes\u00ae America\u2019s Best Employers  PEOPLE\u00ae Companies That Care  IND123 Basic Purpose     To research, evaluate, design, implement, and maintain system and product solutions, applying knowledge of engineering principles. To provide technical direction and engineering support for projects and infrastructure. Develops basic knowledge of industry technologies/competition, concepts and trends. Responsible for implementing, configuring, managing, and troubleshooting the underlying technologies related to Navy Federal's virtualization strategy. Engineer must be able to perform basic to difficult levels of administrative and technical tasks. Accuracy, effective communication, being a strong team player, and participation in a 24x7 on-call support rotation is critical. Responsibilities: Your success with attaining and performing the required skills and abilities will be enhanced if they consist of the following: \u2022Anticipate and adjust for potential impact \u2022Apply engineering principles to the design and enhancement of systems \u2022Document new system components, or modifications to existing components \u2022Ensure the security and integrity of system an