nd procedures, problem resolution, and troubleshooting techniques \u2022VMware VCP or VCAP at an enterprise level \u2022Windows Server \u2022Linux Server \u2022Strong knowledge of programming languages (PowerShell, JavaScript, Python) \u2022Strong knowledge of Cisco Unified Computing System (UCS) administration \u2022Strong knowledge of networking and storage concepts (VLANs, Trunking, FC, VSANs, Zoning) \u2022Flexibility and adaptability to handle competing work demands \u2022Strong detailed-oriented attributes Desired Knowledge, Skills and/or Abilities: \u2022Knowledge of VMware Virtualization technologies \u2022Knowledge and experience with Windows servers \u2022Knowledge and experience with Linux servers \u2022Knowledge and experience with cloud deployment technologies Hours : Monday through Friday, TBD and on-call Availability 24x7 on a rotational on-call basis Location:  Vienna, VA (Headquarters) or Pensacola, FL  Equal Employment Opportunity     Navy Federal values, celebrates, and enacts diversity in the workplace. Navy Federal takes affirmative action to employ and advance in employment qualified individuals with disabilities, disabled veterans, Armed Forces service medal veterans, recently separated veterans, and other protected veterans. EOE/AA/M/F/Veteran/Disability Disclaimer Navy Federal reserves the right to fill this role at a higher/lower grade level based on business need. Bank Secrecy Act Remains cognizant of and adheres to Navy Federal policies and procedures, and regulations pertaining to the Bank Secrecy Act.     Recommended skills  Storage (Computing)  Windows Servers  Information Security  Time Management  Complex Problem Solving  V Mware Virtualization  "}
